data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Recommended Workspace: This refers to the optimal area within which you should position your coordinates for the best performance and safety. It defines the region most suitable for operating the robot.
Quill Angle: This is the angle of the flange relative to the direction of Joint 2. A quill angle of 0 degrees means the flange is aligned with the end of Joint 2, right in the center. Range:(-150):150
Quill Parallel: When this checkbox is selected, the tool is automatically adjusted to remain parallel to the robot's base, regardless of the movement or position of the robot's joints.
Flange Spread: This refers to the size of the object, measured in millimeters, that the robot's flange or gripper is designed to handle or grasp. Range:0:49
